		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:22px;color:#00aeef"><strong>WHAT’S NEW?</strong></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="center" valign="top"><img src="http://www.ncsthechallenge.org/images/staffing/Images/ncstc_hr_290914.jpg" width="550" height="22" border="0" style="display:block"></td>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		</tr>
		
		<tr>
		
		<td width="25" align="left" valign="top"></td>
		
		<td width="550" align="left" valign="top" style="font-family:'Century Gothic',Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:15px;line-height:20px;color:#222222">
		
			<table width="550" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0"><tbody><tr>
			
			<td align="left" valign="top"><p><strong>The Staffing Website</strong><br>
			We rolled out parts of our new Staffing Website in 2014 and in 2015 we will continue to add more sections to make the Staffing Website even more accessible to seasonal staff. Watch out for our new Application Form and Event Booking System!</p>
			
			<p><strong>Successful Pilot Waves</strong><br>
			In summer 2014 we ran several ‘Pilot Waves’ to test new ideas like accommodation in a ‘tented village’ and carrying out the NCS: Real Challenge Action during a consecutive fourth week in August. Feedback from young people and seasonal staff about these have been so positive that we are now introducing many of them for 2015. Watch this space as more detailed information about different wave lengths and formats will become available in April.</p>
			
			<p><strong>A New Season To Work In!</strong><br>
			If you miss NCS during those cold winter months, we’ve got some good news! We’re launching a February half-term programme. Much like autumn programme, the February half-term one is a condensed version of the summer programme. More information about roles available in February is available here.</p></td>
			
			</tr></tbody></table>
		</td>
		
